
[1]informing

   INFORM'ING, ppr. Giving notice or intelligence; telling.

   1. Communicating facts by way of accusation.

     Informing officer, is an officer whose duty it is to inform against
       persons for breaches of law, as an attorney-general, a sheriff,
                         constable, or grand juror.

        A common informer, is any person who informs against another.
     __________________________________________________________________

